  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "@elopio posted [a review of `ERC20Snapshot`](https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/draft-review-erc20snapshot/302) in the forum a year ago. Some of the comments are about the API and this is the moment to review it, before we release 3.0. Sorry I keep adding things! Here goes each individual comment from the review that concerns the API:\r\n\r\n- [ ] the name `ERC20Snapshot` is not good. To be fully explicit, a better name would be `ERC20WithOnDemandSnapshots`.\r\n- [ ] snapshot is not a nice verb. I suggest to rename the `snapshot` function to `makeSnapshot`, the `Snapshot` event to `SnapshotMade`, and never ever say snapshotted.\r\n- [ ] Snapshot ids start at 1. This is weird, and we are more used to 0-indexing so it could lead to off-by-1 errors.\r\n- [ ] Anybody can call `snapshot`. There should be a role for this. (NB: This function was public but has now been made internal.)\r\n- [ ] I dislike `balanceOf`, but `balanceOfAt` is terrible. I suggest `getBalanceFromSnapshot`. I suggest `totalSupplyAt` -> `getTotalSupplyFromSnapshot`. `_valueAt` -> `_valueFromSnapshot`.",
